main event: A sighting of two unidentified aerial objects observed in Waco, Texas on 25 August 1952.
interesting points: The witnesses reported the objects to be made of aluminum, The objects were flying in formation at a high speed exceeding 1000 miles per hour, The sighting lasted for approximately 5 seconds, The objects made a sharp right turn and accelerated at a tremendous rate, The assistant vice-president of the First National Bank of Waco noted he was trained in identification problems.
sighted object: two aluminum objects flying in formation
witness description: assistant vice-president of the First National Bank of Waco
